To find the mean of a set of numbers, we add up all the numbers and divide by the count of numbers. In this case, we need to add up the six test scores and divide the sum by 6 to get the mean.
Step 1: Add up all the test scores:
$$\begin{align*}
70 + 80 + 90 + 75 + 80 + 85
\end{align*}$$

Step 2: Divide the sum by the number of test scores (6):
$$\begin{align*}
\frac{70 + 80 + 90 + 75 + 80 + 85}{6}
\end{align*}$$

Step 3: Simplify the numerator by grouping numbers that add up to 80:
$$\begin{align*}
\frac{(70 + 90) + 80 + 80 + (75 + 85)}{6} &= \frac{(80 + 80) + 80 + 80 + (80 + 80)}{6}
\end{align*}$$

Step 4: Factor out 80 from the numerator:
$$\begin{align*}
\frac{6 \cdot 80}{6}
\end{align*}$$

Step 5: Cancel out the common factor (6) in the numerator and denominator:
$$\begin{align*}
80
\end{align*}$$
The mean of the six test scores is $\boxed{80}$.

